<TITLE> Stocks fall sharply in opening trade </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 02 (bdnews24.com)The market opened with a sharp fall seen in the general index on the week's first trading day. It gained some points after the first hour of trade started but declined again. The DGEN or general index was at 2855.84, down 115.27 points or 3.87 percent at 12.52 pm. The DSI or all share price index was at 2418.24, down 93.07 points or 3.70 percent. At 12.52 pm 11 issues had gained, 178 declined and 9 remained unchanged. At 12.58 pm, UCBL emerged first among the top ten shares by value, though its share price had declined sharply. It was selling at Tk 4839 from Thursday's closing price of Tk 5147 BRAC Bankone of the most active sharesalso fell, selling at Tk 1536 from Tk 1579.50 at Thursday's close of trade. Islami Bank Perpetual Bond was selling at Tk 1499.75 from Thursday's closing price of Tk 1636. Market major, Power Grid Company of Bangladesh was selling at Tk 678 from Tk 694.75 at Thursday's closing. Square Pharma was selling at Tk 3187.5 from Thursday's closing price of Tk 3320. Other scrips in the top ten shares board by valueUttara Bank, Grameen1 Mutual Fund, BOC Bangladesh, Islami Bank and Social Investment Bankalso fell. bd
